I think you guys have the wrong idea about this server. The point is not that you're paying the extra thirty dollars for just a bit of (relatively) trivial coding.<P>What you're paying for is a large, full-time, <B>paid</B> GM staff that is always available and active on the server. A staff that will do dynamic events on a frequent basis, especially as compared to a regular server.  staff that can answer petitions in minutes instead of hours.<P>The cost is in hiring all these people and paying them to sit around and provide what is, without a doubt, a highly premium service.<P>--------------------<P>That a man is a great warrior may not be measured by how many lives he has taken.<P>He is great in that, no matter how many fall before his blade, each is regretted as the first was.
