This venture will fail.  At 10 dollars a month, people will tolerate a few bugs here and there.  Verant stretches that limit with their crappy code, but at ten dollars, people are too lazy to cancel the service.  <P>At fourty dollars a month, noone will tolerate the amount of bugs that will exist on this legends server.  This is similar to DSL in America.  The quality of service is so bad that most people cancel it in the first month and go back to their 56K modem.  The 56K modem may be a bit slow, but it is very reliable.  As a result, DSL has been a big failure so far and is the reason why telecom companies are in the crapper.<P>The GM events have alot of one time code so it can't be reworked in the next patch, because it never gets used again after the GM event is over.  The GM events I've participated in should be called bug day events.  Alot of crash while zoning and link death.<P>They would probably be more successful just raising the overall price to 40 dollars a month for everybody.  Perish the thought.
